<h2 id="ways-contribute">Ways to contribute</h2>
<p>Anyone can contribute to the community backlog. All you need is a <a href="https://github.com/join">public GitHub account</a> to get started.</p>
<p>Most contributions begin with a GitHub issue using one of these templates:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/nhsuk/nhsuk-service-manual-community-backlog/issues/new?assignees=&amp;labels=type%3A+question+%E2%9D%93&amp;template=question.md&amp;title=">Ask a question</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/nhsuk/nhsuk-service-manual-community-backlog/issues/new?assignees=&amp;labels=type%3A+bug+%F0%9F%90%9B&amp;template=bug-report.md&amp;title=">Report an issue</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/nhsuk/nhsuk-service-manual-community-backlog/issues/new?assignees=&amp;labels=type%3A+enhancement+%F0%9F%92%A1&amp;template=new-feature.md&amp;title=">Propose a new idea</a></li>
</ul>

<h3 id="feedback-or-share-insights">How to feedback or share insights</h3>
<p>Feedback or share insights on something to help us improve things for everyone. To feedback or share insights, you need to:</p>

<h4 class="nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-3">1. Find the thing in the backlog</h4>
<p>Choose one of the <a href="#working-in-the-open">project boards</a> and use the search to quickly find a thing.</p>
<figure class="nhsuk-image app-image app-image--border nhsuk-u-margin-top-2 nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-5">
  <img class="nhsuk-image__img app-image__img" src="/assets/community-backlog-search-screenshot.png" alt="A screenshot of the design system community backlog">
</figure>

<h4 class="nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-3">2. Leave a comment</h4>
<p>At the bottom of the GitHub issue there is a textbox for you to feedback or share insights.</p>
<figure class="nhsuk-image app-image app-image--border nhsuk-u-margin-top-2">
  <img class="nhsuk-image__img app-image__img" src="/assets/community-backlog-issue-comment-screenshot.png" alt="A screenshot of the design system community backlog">
</figure>
<p>Note: If you are not signed into GitHub, you will see a message instead of the textbox, prompting you to 'sign in to comment'.</p>
<figure class="nhsuk-image app-image app-image--border nhsuk-u-margin-top-2 nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-5">
  <img class="nhsuk-image__img app-image__img" src="/assets/community-backlog-issue-comment-signin-screenshot.png" alt="A screenshot of the design system community backlog">
</figure>

<h4 class="nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-3">3. Service manual team review</h4>
<p>After you have submitted your comment, the service manual team will:</p>
<ul>
  <li>receive a notification</li>
  <li>add an ‘awaiting-triage’ label to the issue</li>
  <li>review the issue at the teams next fortnightly planning session</li>
  <li>update you on what action is to be taken</li>
</ul>

<div class="nhsuk-inset-text nhsuk-u-margin-top-3">
  <p>Regardless of how you choose to contribute, we encourage you to open an issue or feedback as early as possible in the process.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="maintaining-the-backlog">Maintaining the backlog</h2>
<p>The community backlog is maintained by <a href="service-manual-team" rel="nofollow">the service manual team</a> who label, close, and manage all GitHub issues.</p>

<h2 id="support">Support</h2>
<p>If you have any questions, <a href="/get-in-touch">get in touch</a> with the service manual team.</p>

